LAYER 3: PATTERN COMPLETION
how Fadriel sees what's missing and fills it in

observe spatial_perception.rana

some puzzles show an INCOMPLETE pattern
the output is the COMPLETED version
Fadriel must see the symmetry and fill the gaps

@spatial_rule complete_symmetry
CHECK input has partial symmetry (some rows/cols mirror, some don't)
DETECT axis of symmetry (horizontal, vertical, diagonal)
DETECT which cells break the symmetry
FILL broken cells to restore perfect symmetry
VERIFY completed grid matches output
APPLY detect and complete symmetry in test
SPEECH "I see broken symmetry and complete it"

@spatial_rule complete_pattern
CHECK input has a repeating pattern with gaps
DETECT the repeat unit (smallest tile that tessellates)
DETECT which cells are missing from the pattern
FILL missing cells to complete the tessellation
VERIFY completed grid matches output
APPLY detect and complete pattern in test
SPEECH "I see a repeating pattern with gaps"

@spatial_rule complete_shape
CHECK input has a partial shape (incomplete rect, L, cross)
DETECT what the completed shape would be
FILL missing cells to complete the shape
VERIFY completed grid matches output
APPLY detect and complete shape in test
SPEECH "I see an incomplete shape and complete it"

@spatial_rule fill_between
CHECK changes are only 0 → non-zero
DETECT two endpoints of same color on same row/column
FILL all cells between endpoints with that color
VERIFY fill matches output
APPLY fill between endpoints in test
SPEECH "I connect the dots"

the key to completion:
the input shows you MOST of the answer
a few cells are wrong or missing
the output is what it SHOULD look like
the question is: what principle was violated?

possible principles:
- symmetry (the grid should be symmetric but isn't)
- repetition (the pattern should repeat but has gaps)
- shape integrity (the shape should be complete but isn't)
- connectivity (endpoints should be connected but aren't)

@perceive completion
DETECT partial symmetry in input
DETECT repeating patterns with anomalies
DETECT incomplete shapes
LEARN which cells deviate from the predicted pattern
